<manpage>
    <sample url="sdk\operating_system\crt\libc\stdio\getchar">getchar</sample>
    <title> getchar, getwchar</title>
    <volume>C 运行库函数</volume>
    <routine_idx> stio_idx.htm </routine_idx>

    <description>
        <para>从标准输入流中取一个字符。</para>
    </description>

    <syntax>
        <return_val>int</return_val>
        <func_name>getchar</func_name>
        <NoArguments/>
        <parameters>
            <func_param>
                <param_type>void</param_type>
            </func_param>
        </parameters>
    </syntax>

    <syntax>
        <return_val>wint_t</return_val>
        <func_name>getwchar</func_name>
        <parameters>
            <func_param>
                <param_type>void</param_type>
            </func_param>
        </parameters>
    </syntax>

    <return>
        <para>返回读取的字符。读取出错或流已结束，getchar返回EOF，getwchar返回WEOF。对于getchar，调用ferror可以检测是哪种错误。</para>
    </return>

    <remarks>
        <para>两个函数都是从标准输入流的当前位置读入一个字符，并且相关文件指针加1（一个字符单位），指向下一个字符。getwchar是getchar的宽字符版本。如果文件流以文本模式打开，getwchar按多字节字符方式读字符串；如果以二进制模式打开，按宽字符方式读字符串。</para>
        <table>
            <th>
                <td>函数</td>
                <td>描述</td>
            </th>
            <tr>
                <td>getchar</td>
                <td>可以作为一个函数或一个宏执行</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>getwchar</td>
                <td>是getchar的宽字符版本，根据流的打开方式是文本模式还是二进制模式读取一个多字节字符或一个宽字节字符</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </remarks>

    <requirements>
        <routine>
            <routine_name>getchar</routine_name>
            <headerfile>stdio.h</headerfile>
            <compatibility>ANSI, Windows 2000, Elastos </compatibility>
        </routine>
        <routine>
            <routine_name>getwchar</routine_name>
            <headerfile>stdio.h</headerfile>
            <compatibility>ANSI, Windows 2000, Elastos </compatibility>
        </routine>
    </requirements>

    <example>
<pre>
//==========================================================================
// Copyright (c) 2000-2004,  Elastos, Inc.  All Rights Reserved.
//==========================================================================

/* getchar.cpp: This program uses getchar to read a single line
 * of input from stdin, places this input in buffer, then
 * terminates the string before printing it to the screen.
 */

#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main()
{
    char buffer[81];
    int i, ch;

    printf(&quot;Enter a line: &quot;);

    /* Read in single line from &quot;stdin&quot;: */
    for (i = 0; (i &lt; 80) &amp;&amp; ((ch = getchar()) != EOF) &amp;&amp; (ch != &apos;\n&apos;); i++)
        buffer[i] = (char)ch;

    /* Terminate string with null character: */
    buffer[i] = &apos;\0&apos;;
    printf(&quot;%s\n&quot;, buffer);

    return 0;
}
</pre>
    </example>
<result>
Enter a line: This is a test
This is a test
</result>

    

